VTB to Buy Russian Rail Stake in TransCreditBank By End 2013

-- B y   A n t o n   D o r o s h e v
-- 
2011-07-15T15:15:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/vtb-to-buy-russian-rail-stake-in-transcreditbank-by-end-2013.html
VTB Group,  Russia ’s second-biggest
lender, agreed to buy OAO  Russian Railways ’ stake OAO
TransCreditBank in two stages, starting with 29 percent for
about 16.5 billion rubles ($587 million), said Yury Novozhilov,
the head of acquisition target.  VTB will buy the first stake this month and the remaining
25 percent from July 1, 2012, to the end of 2013, the Russian
rail monopoly said today in a statement.  The Moscow-based lender will pay 24.4 rubles a share for
the first stake, while the price for the second will be based on
performance indicators, VTB said in a separate statement.  The deal values Russian Railways’ 54.4 percent at about 40
billion, TransCreditBank’s Novozhilov said. The second stake may
cost 13.5 billion rubles plus a share in TransCreditBank’s
profit for Russian Rail, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anton Doroshev in Moscow at 
